The 3D comet model, cg-dlr_spg-shap7-v1.0_200Kfacets.obj, is derived from one
distributed with shapeViewer. It is licensed under the Simplified BSD Liense,
which allows for use, modification, and distribution under specified terms.
Full license details: https://opensource.org/licenses/BSD-2-Clause
This research has made use of the scientific software shapeViewer
(www.comet-toolbox.com).
Reference: Vincent et al. shapeViewer, a sofware for the scientific mapping and
morphological analysis of small bodies, LPSC, (2018).

All of the included comet images (under data/J80) were created by extracting jpg 
images from the European Space Agency's Rosetta NAC .IMG files, using USGS ISIS
tools. These image files are distributable under the Creative Commons
Attribution-ShareAlike 4.0 International License.

